Nigeria’s SEC Vows to Clear Bank Agreements, Guardian Reports

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-08-23T08:57:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/nigeria-s-sec-vows-to-clear-bank-agreements-guardian-reports.html
Nigeria’s Securities and Exchange
Commission will approve the transaction agreements signed by
five rescued banks before a Sept. 30 recapitalization deadline,
the Guardian reported, citing the regulator’s director-general,
Aruma Oteh.  The lenders, including Intercontinental Bank Plc, Union
Bank Nigeria Plc, Oceanic Bank International Plc, Equitorial
Trust Bank Ltd. and Finbank Plc, have signed agreements with
investors, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 